Feature: Evanesco (Vanishing Spell)

    Makes the target vanish.

    Pronunciation:
        /ɛvəˈnɛskoʊ/ EV-ə-NES-koh
    Seen/mentioned:
        Used in Order of the Phoenix by Snape to make Harry's potions disappear
        from his cauldron. In addition, when Fred and George were showing off
        their puking pastilles, Lee Jordan cleared the bucket of vomit with the
        Evanesco spell.
    Suggested etymology: - 
    Notes:
        According to Minerva McGonagall, in Deathly Hallows, Vanished objects
        and organisms go "into non-being, which is to say, everything."